summary: Madison Keys' Wimbledon journey came to an abrupt end due to a leg injury. In the third set against Jasmine Paolini, Keys retired from the match, leaving Paolini to advance to the quarterfinals. The injury caused visible distress, with Keys leaving the court in tears. The injury prevented Keys from serving for the match twice. Despite the unfortunate turn of events, Keys has remained positive, expressing her determination to return stronger. She even highlighted the supportive role of her fiancé, Bjorn Fratangelo, who complements her well both on and off the court.

name: French elections
summary: France's political landscape is undergoing a significant shift as the results of parliamentary elections emerge. The far-right National Rally, led by Jordan Bardella, has made impressive gains, potentially positioning him as the youngest prime minister in French history. However, a surprise surge by left-wing parties has left the election outcome uncertain. Leftists narrowly beat out the far right in the first round, forcing a battle for control of the parliament. The stakes are high for French President Emmanuel Macron and his centrist party, En Marche!, as they seek to maintain their majority. The results will have a major impact on Macron's ability to implement his policies and the overall direction of France's future. The diverse range of voters and their motivations in supporting different political parties highlight the complexities and divisions within French society.

While Swiatek reached the third round with a victory over Petra Martic, she was unable to overcome Putintseva's determined play. name: Abhishek Sharma
summary: In the second T20I match against Zimbabwe, Indian batsman Abhishek Sharma made history by becoming the third-fastest player to score a century in T20I cricket, surpassing Rohit Sharma's previous record. Sharma's maiden century, which he achieved in just 47 balls, played a crucial role in India's comprehensive victory by 100 runs. Sharma's father revealed that he had reminded his son to focus on hitting sixes, which ultimately led to his impressive performance. Following Sharma's record-breaking century, former Indian cricketer Yuvraj Singh expressed his emotions and congratulated him. The victory against Zimbabwe has helped India draw level in the five-game series.
